{
  "text": "Data integration is a widely studied topic in database research and can be described as the combination of data from different sources so that users can have a unified view of such data (Lenzerini et al., 2002) , aiming mainly at an easier access and re-use of data [CITATION_1] . In spite of the great number of works on this subject, there still are unresolved issues. More specifically, the adoption of business process modeling (BPM) and service oriented architectures (SOA) by organizations, and the highly heterogeneous computer environments present new challenges and opportunities for data integration approaches.",
  "correct_citation": {
    "[CITATION_1]": "9552382"
